content:
To implement "on press" functionality for Google Maps navigation in React Native, you can use the following steps:

1. First, you need to install the "react-native-maps" package. You can do this by running the following command in your terminal:
```java
npm install react-native-maps
```
2. After installing the package, you need to import the MapView component from "react-native-maps" in your code. You can do this by adding the following line at the top of your file:
```python
import MapView from 'react-native-maps';
```
3. Next, you can create a MapView component in your render method and add a Marker component to it. The Marker component will represent the location that the user wants to navigate to. Here's an example:
```php
<MapView
  style={{ flex: 1 }}
  region={{
    latitude: 37.78825,
    longitude: -122.4324,
    latitudeDelta: 0.0922,
    longitudeDelta: 0.0421,
  }}
>
  <Marker
    coordinate={{
      latitude: 37.78825,
      longitude: -122.4324,
    }}
    onPress={() => {
      // Your navigation logic goes here
    }}
  />
</MapView>
```
4. In the onPress function of the Marker component, you can implement your navigation logic using a library like "react-native-navigation" or "react-navigation". You can use the latitude and longitude values of the Marker component's coordinate prop to determine the destination of the navigation.

Here's an example using the "react-native-navigation" library:
```javascript
import { Navigation } from 'react-native-navigation';

// ...

<Marker
  coordinate={{
    latitude: 37.78825,
    longitude: -122.4324,
  }}
  onPress={() => {
    Navigation.navigate('NavigationScreen', {
      latitude: 37.78825,
      longitude: -122.4324,
    });
  }}
/>
```
In this example, the onPress function calls the "Navigation.navigate" method with the name of the screen that you want to navigate to (in this case, "NavigationScreen") and an object containing the latitude and longitude values of the destination.

You can then use these values in the destination screen to set the region of a MapView component or to call the Google Maps API to get directions to the destination.
